in highly taxed sweden even children 
with more than 160 in the bank must pay income tax starting next 
year 
you are a tax subject as soon as you are born senior 
treasury official urban eriksson said tuesday confirming a 
newspaper report that said children with savings accounts will have 
to file tax returns on their interest 
until now most childrens accounts were sheltered but that 
will change when a new tax reform law takes effect in 1991 
the svenska dagbladet newspaper said some parents have been 
using their childrens accounts to shelter their own savings from 
taxes 
