<TEXT>
a tangle of problems awaits president bushs 
proposal to send 800 million to bolster new democracies in panama 
and nicaragua and threatens to delay the measure past the 
presidents easter deadline 
bush met with congressional leaders tuesday to press for quick 
action on the package deputy secretary of state lawrence 
eagleburger argued on capitol hill that it is crucial to the 
survival of the new democratic governments of panamanian president 
guillermo endara and nicaraguas presidentelect violeta chamorro 
early success is going to be fundamental to whether mr 
endara and mrs chamorro are going to make it eagleburger told 
the senate appropriations subcommittee on foreign operations 
bush said the aid not only would demonstrate tangible benefits 
of democracy but would turn up the heat on cubas fidel castro 
the hemispheres lone communist holdout 
id like to see him shift from that highly militarized island 
and let democracy have a chance he told lawmakers at a white 
