million for panama is a oneshot economic infusion that wont 
likely be repeated and that nicaraguas 300 million in aid wont 
flow until leftist president daniel ortega fully turns over power 
to mrs chamorro 
but he seemed to acknowledge the tough job ahead and several 
senators pointed to a thicket of potential problems that could 
delay the package beyond april 5 when congress recesses for easter 
the most immediate problem is how to pay for the package the 
administration is negotiating with congress on its proposal to cut 
pentagon spending to free money for the aid bill sen robert 
kasten rwis said he believed those talks would be completed in 
the next two days 
sen patrick leahy dvt the appropriations subcommittee 
chairman said it was almost certain that some lawmakers would seek 
to cut us military aid to el salvador to signal displeasure over 
that governments failure to bring to justice the killers of six 
jesuit priests 
nicaragua still must find a way to reintegrate the contra 
rebels who have fought the government for the past decade into 
