of dubious value the report said 
however the association said its analysis of more than 15 years 
of research found that substance abuse treatment increases 
employment decreases crime increases productivity and reduces 
health costs 
one study by the university of california at los angeles 
estimated that for every dollar spent for treatment services 
1154 in social costs is saved 
there are no great unsolved mysteries to drug and alcohol 
treatment the real mystery is why we spend so little treating 
dependency and so much paying for its effects crime violence 
illness the breakup of families poverty and death gustafson said 
for comparison he estimated it costs 50000 to keep an inmate 
in prison for a year and 100000 to care for an aids patient for a 
year while outpatient drug treatment costs about 3000 per 
patient 
the governments national institute on alcohol abuse and 
alcoholism estimated that 18 million adults abuse alcohol and that 
10 million of those are alcoholics 
the report said 41 states and the district of columbia reported 
that a total of 14 million people 123525 of them under 18 
receive alcohol and drug treatment each year 
those states estimated that 106 million others are in need of 
such treatment 
the report said that 66766 people in 44 states are on waiting 
lists for treatment about half have been waiting for at least a 
month 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

