the bass brothers of texas won a battle of 
millionaires when voters rejected a referendum that would have 
required a huge hog farm to build a 10 million facility to treat 
manure 
weld county residents voted 14706 to 6334 to defeat a 
referendum on the issue county officials said 
national farms inc owned by the brothers from fort worth 
texas opened the massive hogprocessing operation 20 miles east of 
greeley last year when it reaches full capacity the facility will 
process 300000 hogs a year and will be one of the largest hog 
plants in the nation 
