quickly said chuang suohang a fellow at the institute for 
national policy research 
although concern about the nations political future has caused 
lees popularity to drop somewhat from his earlier approval ratings 
of more than 80 percent he still can count on widespread support 
and good will 
part of his popularity stems from his being the first native 
taiwanese to lead the government and the ruling party formed 95 
years ago on the chinese mainland by sun yatsen 
he has frequently toured the island to visit farmers soldiers 
and other groups to build up personal support 
lee was elevated from vice president to head of government in 
january 1988 when president chiang chingkuo the son of chiang 
kaishek died and ended four decades of family rule on taiwan 
in the last year of his life chiang chingkuo ended martial law 
and a ban on opposition political parties in a political 
liberalization program that lee says he will continue 
because he is a native taiwanese lee is viewed warily by many 
old guard nationalist conservatives who still dream of returning 
victoriously to rule the chinese mainland 
lee has carefully reiterated the nationalist claim to represent 
all china but he also has pursued a more pragmatic policy to 
increase unofficial contacts with the chinese mainland 
he has yet to allow direct trade as demanded by many businessmen 
