here are excerpts from recent editorials in newspapers 
throughout the country 
march 17 
grants pass ore daily courier on earthfriendly products 
companies should try hard work instead of hype in trying to cash 
in on the growing trend among consumers to buy socalled 
earthfriendly items 
industry must research new ways to produce and use biodegradable 
materials in packaging and to reuse materials that arent 
biodegradable such as glass they also need to phase out products 
that damage the environment such as hairsprays containing 
chemicals that destroy the earths protective ozone layer 
unfortunately all many companies are doing these days is 
slapping labels with misleading or outright false claims on their 
products rather than looking for ways to honestly help 
environmentally conscious shoppers 
plastic trash bags suddenly turn into degradable bags and a 
can of aerosol hair spray becomes ozone friendly even though 
it contains chemicals that cause smog and air pollution 
regulators need to force manufacturers to verify their claims 
just as they did when firms claimed to have cures for baldness 
this time the goal is much more important than growing hair though 
its obvious from the governments halfhearted attempts at 
cleaning up the environment that any real progress will have to 
come from grassroots movements people will have to change their 
lifestyles and demand that politicians and companies change their 
ways too 
</TEXT>
