was speaking on the first full day of independence for namibia 
which since 1915 had been a territory of south africa 
crocker spent eight years negotiating independence for namibia 
and had to work out a series of complicated deals to bring it about 
these included persuading angolas marxist government to send 
home 50000 cuban troops who were helping it battle antimarxist 
guerrillas and south african fighters the angolans also agreed to 
close bases of the african national congress the nationalist group 
fighting south africas government 
