<TEXT>
a house panel voted wednesday to restrict the 
sale and possession of usmade assault rifles and require a 
minimum 10year sentence for a person carrying such a weapon while 
committing a crime 
president bush last year banned import of the semiautomatic 
rifles the bill approved by the house judiciary subcommittee on 
crime would require the administration to extend the ban to 
domesticmade versions which the president determines have no 
sporting purpose 
subcommittee chairman bill hughes dnj said it makes no 
sense to ban imports and not the american assault weapons that 
account for twothirds of those in circulation 
theres no question but that assault weapons are being used 
with increased frequency by drug dealers criminals and mental 
incompetents to carry out acts of violence hughes said 
the term assault weapons refers to semiautomatic versions of 
automatic rifles originally developed for military use 
the bill would not affect the ownership or transfer of existing 
weapons and it would not apply to handguns 
the 10year minimum penalty would apply when an assault weapon 
is used or carried during a violent crime or drug crime 
the bill next goes to the full house judiciary committee 
</TEXT>
