angolan rebels claimed wednesday they 
were bombarding two major garrisons in southern angola and had 
pinned down troops of the marxist government 
a brief military statement released in lisbon and signed by the 
rebels military information chief col zacarias mundombe said 
the strategic mavinga airstrip and cuito cuanavale came under 
intense bombardment 
it gave no details of casualties or damage but said the shelling 
prevented government soldiers at mavinga from leaving their 
positions 
in separate attacks in the northern province of uige the 
statement said rebels killed 23 government soldiers destroyed 
sovietbuilt military vehicles and captured various weapons 
fighting in angolas 15yearold civil war has intensified since 
the government launched a major offensive against the unita rebels 
in their southern heartland in december 
clashes have been especially bitter around mavinga 700 miles 
southeast of the capital luanda 
the usbacked unita the national union for the total 
independence of angola has been waging a war since 1975 to force 
the sovietaided government into a powersharing agreement 
