<TEXT>
the state department accused the burmese 
government wednesday of engaging in arbitrary interference in 
the lives of many burmese citizens by forcibly removing them from 
their homes 
deputy spokesman richard boucher said burmese military 
authorities have relocated often on short notice residents of 
some burmese cities particularly rangoon to new areas outside 
those locations 
in many cases the new housing areas are illprepared lacking 
sanitary and other facilities and are isolated by distance and 
lack of regular transport he said 
while some of those being forcibly relocated appear to be 
squatters we understand that many are legitimate owners of houses 
and property 
there have been reports of deaths as a result of the 
relocations most appear to have taken place in areas where there 
has been strong antigovernment sentiment he said 
whatever the motives for the relocations they appear to have 
been carried out without due regard for the interest safety and 
rights of those involved boucher said 
we call upon the burmese military regime to respect the 
fundamental and legitimate civil rights of the burmese people 
including refraining from arbitrary interference in their lives and 
property 
