tens of thousands of black workers stayed home from work and 
school and attended rallies in black townships in honor of the 69 
blacks killed by police during a 1960 demonstration at sharpeville 
a black township outside johannesburg 
the sharpeville shootings were a turning point for the african 
national congress which broke with decades of nonviolent protest 
to fight south africas whiterun government during the past 
decade a national strike has been called each year to commemorate 
the dead and many employers now give their workers the day off 
