distribute including canned fruit egg mix and peanut butter 
provide a balanced diet and are similar in quality to food sold in 
supermarkets 
the food is distributed through usda programs to 143000 indians 
and 271000 women children and elderly people each month 
the canned beef and pork is covered with fat when its opened 
because its cooked in the can so that it can be stored without 
refrigeration nelsen said 
the meat which is inspected during and after processing cannot 
contain more than 18 percent fat and usually has about 15 percent 
she said 
ground beef by comparison usually contains 20 percent to 30 
percent fat said pat daniel an agriculture department nutrionist 
the meat may be eaten directly from the can but its meant to 
be used in recipes with other ingredients like the stews or 
casseroles served to reporters nelsen said 
