the fbi released composite drawings wednesday of 
the two thieves who committed the art theft of the century at the 
gardner museum when they stole 11 priceless paintings and prints 
even before a 1 million reward was posted tipsters began 
calling the isabella stewart gardner museum and the fbi hinting 
they knew where the artworks could be found officials said 
the public was allowed inside the museum wednesday for the first 
time since the crime with two of its looted rooms now behind 
police barricades 
two men wearing police uniforms talked their way into the 
museum early sunday and made off with 11 paintings and prints by 
such artists as rembrandt and degas they also swiped an ancient 
chinese vase and a gilded eagle from a napoleonic flag pole 
the fbi composite drawings showed two white men in policemens 
hats one was depicted with gold wirerimmed glasses a strong jaw 
and was described as being in his late 20s to early 30s with dark 
hair and eyes medium build and 5foot7 to 5foot10 the other 
shown with pronounced cheekbones was thought to be in his early to 
mid30s with dark hair and eyes 180 pounds and 6feet or 6foot1 
the composites showed both with mustaches and without because 
authorities believe they might have worn fake mustaches during the 
robbery 
the items taken from what was the late mrs gardners personal 
collection are considered too wellknown to be sold on the open 
market and have been estimated to be worth hundreds of millions of 
dollars 
the international auction houses sothebys and christies 
underwrote the 1 million reward tuesday for safe return of the 
works the fbi and the museum were fielding tips around the clock 
and deciding which might be the real thing 
youre generally talking about thieves that are going to be in 
contact with others in criminal circles and thats where it 
generally comes from said fbi agent dennis ocallaghan 
he declined to comment on whether staff at the museum had been 
given lie detector tests but said former employees were being 
questioned a standard practice in such cases 
