<TEXT>
federal authorities filed a 10 million civil 
racketeering lawsuit wednesday against two teamsters locals 
charging that the mafia has dominated the air freight business at 
kennedy airport for two decades 
the lawsuit against locals 295 and 851 of the international 
brotherhood of teamsters alleges a 20year pattern of labor 
racketeering involving extortion illegal payoffs securities fraud 
and obstruction of justice 
it also names current and past union officials and associates of 
the gambino and lucchese crime families many of the defendants are 
either in jail or awaiting trial for organized crime activities 
the suit seeks to recover some 10 million in illegal gains from 
18 defendants remove the mobs influence from the unions and force 
the selection of a courtappointed trustee to assume control of the 
two locals 
the 150plus page complaint names the leadership of the two 
unions and a number of reputed mobsters including anthony 
guerrieri he and reputed gambino boss john gotti were recently 
acquitted of assault charges in a shooting attack on a carpenters 
union leader 
us attorney andrew j maloney said the airfreight business 
is particularly vulnerable because of the nature of the business 
time is of the essence any kind of a slowdown or a strike 
effectively puts them out of business 
james m fox assistant director in charge of the fbis new york 
office said organized crime has owned the airfreight business 
at jfk for decades 
they accomplished this through extortion bribery security 
fraud and obstruction of justice said fox speaking at a news 
conference with maloney at the federal courthouse in brooklyn where 
the lawsuit was filed 
maloney said the mobcontrolled unions extorted payoffs through 
a number of means including threatened and actual strikes and work 
slowdowns 
the air freight forwarders many of them now out of business 
often found it cheaper and quicker to make cash payments to the 
unions rather than oppose them maloney said 
more than half of the air freight coming into the united states 
passes through john f kennedy international airport and the 
illegal activities pushed up air freight costs to consumers the 
authorities said 
no union officials were available to respond to the charges 
according to people who answered the telephones at the locals 
offices 
five weeks ago the federal government sued three organized 
crime groups and six dockworkers union locals accusing the mob of 
exercising a decadeslong stranglehold on the new york and new 
jersey waterfront 
the civil racketeering lawsuit claims that organized crime 
including the gambino family has controlled the international 
longshoremans association locals through murder extortion 
embezzlement of union funds and illegal labor payoffs 
