the senate rejected 5936 a resolution 
wednesday night urging president bush to grant immediate diplomatic 
recognition to the breakaway government of lithuania 
the sponsor sen jesse helms rnc attempted to attach the 
resolution to unrelated legislation but he failed in his attempt 
a symbolic criticism of the administrations caution over 
lithuanias attempt to secede from the soviet union 
democrats helped republican leaders in the opposition to the 
helms proposal 
voting in favor of the resolution were 27 republicans and just 
nine democrats opposed were 44 democrats and 15 republicans 
