white house opposed the resolution yet predicted wrongly that it 
would pass 
the matter should be left to the president sen john 
chafee rri said in support of dole 
all it can do is create mischief said sen dale bumpers 
dark 
lithuanias parliament declared independence from the soviet 
union on march 11 and its fledgling government has been seeking 
recognition from other nations 
soviet president mikhail gorbachev however has declared the 
indepenence decree illegal though gorbachev has said he would not 
use force soviet troops have been conducting exercises in the 
area and gorbachev on wednesday issued a directive to lithuanians 
to turn in their firearms 
lithuania was one of the provinces of the russian czar before 
the 1917 bolshevik revolution it was able to establish its 
independence along with the neighbiring baltic states of estonia 
and latvia in the turmoil that followed the revolution 
indepedence its maintained until the soviet army invaded the 
country in 1940 and attached it to the soviet union 
the united states never withdrew diplomatic recognition from the 
1940 government and the lithuanian community in the united states 
has maintained a legation with full diplomatic standing ever 
since 
the white house has declined to recognize the current government 
although it has urged the soviet union to honor the will of the 
lithuanian people and refrain from using force 
the administrations refusal of recognition has widely been 
attributed to reluctance on the part of the white house to be seen 
opposing gorbachev whom it considers the best hope for progress in 
the soviet union and who is under pressure from several directions 
the sense of the senate resolution offered by helms would 
not have been binding such symbolic resolutions are frequent 
helms congratulated bush for urging moscow to begin talks with 
the lithuanian people but then called on the administration to 
recognize the breakaway governmenet and name a us ambassador to 
lithuania 
more than 100 members of the house earlier sent bush a letter 
urging that lithuania be recognized as an independent nation 
all the lithuanians ask for is moral and political support 
said the letter drafted by reps john miller rwa and richard 
durbin dill 
