who brought civil war to nicaragua uno said the sandinistas 
brought repression and economic misery 
the rhetoric largely disappeared after mrs chamorro won but 
both sides still fear vengeance or resistance by the other 
the sandinistacontrolled legislature approved the measure 
834 the law spells out that none of the highest members of 
state can be subject to any judicial action in nicaraguan courts 
the law is necessary to calm the waters and so that we can 
direct all our efforts to national reconstruction and getting the 
country out of crisis nunez said 
the law guarantees officials immunity from prosecution for 
official actions in the six years since the outgoing 
administrations election in 1984 
those provided with permanent immunity are the president vice 
president ministers and deputy ministers supreme court judges 
the supreme electoral council appeals court judges the army 
commanderinchief and chief of staff and presidents or 
directors of autonomous or government entities 
former national assembly members receive one year of immunity 
under the law 
