<TEXT>
if you were following marilyn vos savants brain 
builder no 115 you wouldnt be reading this 
you would be out getting lost putting yourself in someone 
elses shoes striving in short to make yourself smarter and you 
would have read page 184 of her new book brain building 
exercising yourself smarter which says 
brain builder no 115 get less news 
exercise this week get the news only once a day and only 
from the radio next week get the news only once a day and only 
from the television the following week get the news only once a 
day and only from the newspaper at this point it should be very 
clear why you should turn to the newspaper permanently 
still with us maybe we should explain 
marilyn vos savant believes its sexy to be smart she also 
believes in logic as in smart is sexy marilyn vos savant is the 
smartest person in the world therefore marilyn vos savant is the 
sexiest person in the world 
not that she would say that vos savant is no braggart the 
cover of her book may trumpet the author as the worlds smartest 
person but its not a phrase she seems likely to use 
its a fact though vos savant is listed in the guinness book 
of world records as the person with the highest iq ever recorded 
at age 10 her intelligence quotient was put at 228 which is 
pretty much off the chart as far as the rest of us are concerned 
an iq of 100 is considered normal 
now 43 she has applied her abilities to among other things 
collaboration with her husband dr robert jarvik in artificial 
heart research a novel shes in the midst of writing and an 
advice column she writes each week for parade magazine 
and now she has written a book designed to bring out the latent 
genius that lurks theoretically in all of us she generously 
believes that people are equally endowed between the ears more or 
less but that most of us have become mentally flabby her book 
is presented as a solution a sort of jane fonda workout for the 
brain 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
brain builder no 56 stop relying on maps 
exercise combine an exercise with a day out decide where you 
want to go look only once at the map then go 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
that is followed of course by brain builder no 57 dont 
be afraid to get lost 
there is no small element of wit in vos savants book which 
sometimes reads like a national lampoon parody of selfhelp books 
now this book is not for bloody mathemeticians by any 
means the author said in an interview its not a series of 
tedious algebra exercises of which weve had enough to last us a 
lifetime 
she says that last part with special conviction 
tedious algebra exercises aside vos savant seems to have had 
fun learning and wants to share the wealth her idea of a brain 
tonic is a delicious meal a good mystery a stimulating 
conversation 
to be sure her book includes math problems and other 
browknitters but most tend to be things along the lines of 
take a simple math problem and draw a picture of it or 
cook something with a lot of ingredients but measure by eye 
alone 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
brain builder no 33 start using logic in your everyday life 
exercise assuming youre not underweight the next time 
youre at a restaurant stop eating anything on your plate you 
dont like after the first bite or two and put your knife and fork 
on the plate so the waiter knows youre finished if the waiter 
asks you if anything is wrong tell him quietly and without 
emotion yes i dont like it 
</TEXT>
