fitzgerald sarah vaughan billy eckstine nat king cole as a 
teenager i loved leiber and stoller burt bacharach and hal 
david ive always loved songs and songwriters 
love smokey was completed four times before robinson would 
release it he cant put his finger on it he just knew something 
was missing motown used to be like that every monday morning 
gordy would gather his star writers for a little love critique 
and everyone would pitch songs hard 
you brought your stuff and i had four records that i recorded 
on the temptations and norman whitfield had two and 
hollanddozierholland had three everybody went into that 
meeting man with high hopes recalled robinson 
we were very critical of each other we all wanted each other 
to be the best that we could be 
the past decade has been uneven for this smoothest of soul 
