general motors corp is looking to 
police departments and taxi companies to help support sales figures 
for its newly redesigned chevrolet caprice fullsize car 
the new 1991 caprice which went on sale to the public earlier 
this month is the preferred car of law enforcement agencies 
nationwide gm needs to maintain or increase those sales to hold 
its share of the fullsize car market 
chevrolet sold about 50000 1990model caprices to police 
agencies and taxi fleets chevrolet general manager jim perkins 
said tuesday 
we expect sales of 1991 caprice police and taxis to remain 
about the same he said chevrolet expects to sell about 200000 
caprices during the 1991 model year the first full year of 
production of the new models 
the new caprice shown off tuesday at gms newly refurbished 
willow run assembly plant west of detroit is much more rounded 
than previous caprice models and from some angles appears similar 
to fords mercury sable 
gm spent 85 million for changes at willow run as part of a 
plant modernization program that united auto workers union vice 
president stephen yokich noted on tuesday 
the uaw and the nations big three automakers begin negotiations 
in july to agree on a contract replacing one that expires sept 14 
the capital investment in this plant and the equipment needed 
to start up a new product like this was very substantial yokich 
