invested so much in capital equipment and still managed to lose so 
much in market share 
during the 1980s gm spent about 77 billion mainly for capital 
improvements in upgrading assembly and component plants between 
the end of 1982 and the end of last year gms share of the 
usmade car market dropped 4 percentage points to 48 percent 
one way to boost market share as the industry shrinks in 1990 is 
to hold or increase fleet sales 
