march 1989 
the organizations sales were down 2 percent at 409 billion 
last year and are expected to be flat this year 
rough diamonds yielding polished diamonds of one carat and less 
have been selling at a premium in the open diamond bourses not run 
by the central selling organization for the last several months 
reflecting the strong demand de beers said 
polished diamonds currently fetching between 400 and 3500 a 
carat are experiencing particularly strong demand and will bear 
the brunt of the price increase lamont said 
