<TEXT>
mobil corp said wednesday it was expanding its 
largest us refinery located in beaumont texas at a cost of 300 
million 
the expansion which is scheduled to begin in the third quarter 
of this year will increase the plants capacity to 325000 barrels 
a day of crude oil from the current 285000 barrels 
the bigger refinery will enable mobil the nations 
secondlargest oil company after exxon corp to substantially 
increase production of super unleaded gasoline and distillate 
fuels such as home heating oil the refinery processes various 
grades of crude oil into fuels and other products 
the project which is expected to be completed by the third 
quarter of 1992 also will include the closure of older processing 
units and the use of new technology in existing units 
mobil spokesman john lord said the upgraded plant also will 
incorporate more modern equipment that will reduce emissions of 
sulfur and nitrogen dioxides 
its new processing equipment will help eliminate or 
substantially reduce pollutants normally emitted in the refining 
process lord said 
mobil has four other us refineries in torrance calif 
joliet ill paulsboro nj and chalmette la mobil owns or has 
interests in 22 other refineries around the world its 
secondlargest refinery located in singapore has a capacity of 
200000 barrels a day 
